               <head>Murshidabad and Bengal revenues</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh94006886 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85064915 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh97003385" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4349-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>End-of-month revenue accounts (<term xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">māskabār</term>), with calculations in raqm annotation, for the district (z̤ilʿ) of <placeName>Murshidabad</placeName> in the banglah year 1196/1790, with the latest entries dated 1791 
                        </p>
                        <p>Appended at end are two brief tracts on Bengal revenues for the banglah year 1198
Bengali annotations throughout 
</p>
                        <p>Some personal seals, such as that of <persName key="person_f7239" role="asn">Kishan Charan De </persName>
                        </p>
                        <p>Not foliated; estimated 250 folios approximately </p>
                        <p>Revenue records (<term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">aṣl bāqī</term>), with calculations in raqm annotation, for the province of the <placeName>Bengal khāliṣah-'i sharīfah</placeName>, specifically the cities of <placeName>Murshidabad</placeName> and <placeName>Kolkata</placeName>, in the banglah year 1188 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not foliated; estimated 300 folios approximately </p>
                        <p>Not dated </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="eng">Persian &amp; English</textLang>
                  </msItem>
